			<tr>
				<td><font face="verdana" size="1">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="/quests/default.asp">Quests</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="default.asp?land=2466">Najena</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline3.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<b>Darkforge Armor</b><br><br>
				</td>
			</tr>
				
			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Darkforge Armor</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=31625"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:mif@pobox.com">Manr</a> | 
		                        1/8/2000 5:22:55 AM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2"><P>
Here are the steps required to get information on some Darkforge Armor.  Look under Mistmoore quests to find out about other armor 

pieces.  You can find an undead knight in the same room where Drelzna spawns.  He spawns by a necromancer to the left of you when 

you enter the room.  He looks like a regular skeleton.  He cons blue to me at level 28.  Indifferent to my Dark Elf Shadow Knight.
</P>

<P>
<I>You say,'can you not kill the undead knight please?'<BR>
Soandso says 'Umm... let me think... OK'<BR>
You say,'Thank you much'<BR>
You say,'hail an undead knight'</I><BR>
<B>an undead knight says 'Away from this place of torment.  Make haste and flee before you too share my [gruesome fate]!!'</B><BR>
<I>You say,'What gruesome fate?'</I><BR>
<B>an undead knight says 'I once was a proud Shadowknight, but failed I did in my masters quest. I was sent deep into a Lizard 

fortress within the swamplands. I was to seek out an ancient item for my master. I failed and was captured. The lizards stripped 

me of my [Darkforge Armor] and planned to boil me alive. Before they could do so, I escaped. Upon my return to my masters lair I 

found myself in a [worse predicament].'</B><BR>
<BR> -- Darkforge Armor<BR>
<I>You say,'What Darkforge Armor?'</I><BR>
<B>an undead knight says 'I and I alone have the power to create Darkforge Armor!! It was crafted for me so it is naturally to be 

worn by Shadowknights only. My armor was taken by the Lizardman Crusaders. Unfortunately for them, it lost all power and cannot be 

worn. I would be glad to see it go to good use. Do you [seek thse Darkforge Armor]?'</B><BR>
<BR> -- worse predicamant<BR>
<I>You say,'What worse predicament?'</I><BR>
<B>an undead knight says 'I was torn apart by my master and my bones were given as toys to my masters associates!! I am now only 

half Grandyf the Vile.  My hands, feet and legs were sent here and assembled with spare bones of other unfortunates. Since this is 

the case, I can only [create Darkforge Armor] in the form of Boots, Greaves and Gauntlets. My other bones were sent to the land of 

Mayong!!'</B><BR>
<BR> -- responses to the above answers<BR>
<I>You say,'I seek the Darkforge Armor'<BR>
You say,'Create Darkforge Armor?'</I><BR>
<B>an undead knight says 'Darkforge Gauntlets require both of my Decayed Gauntlets and one Enchanted Platinum Bar. For the 

Darkforge Greaves I will need both Decayed Legplates and two pieces of Melatite from Solusek Mining Company. For the Boots I need 

both my Decayed Boots and two parts of Faiy Dust.'</B><BR>
</P>
<P>
Note that the knight's responses are quoted.  Do not blame me for any spelling and grammatical errors, speak to the knight's 

masters.
</P>
<P>
I am interested to know where I can get the <B>Melatite</B>, <B>Faiy Dust</B>, and <B>Platinum Bar</B>.  More specifically, what 

are the names of the creature from whom I can loot/buy these items and where are they located?
</P>
<P>The Lizardman Crusaders are located in the Temple of Cazic Thule. They are around level 35 and they are Shadow Knights. They 

are somewhat rare spawn in somewhat random locations in the tougher parts of the temple.  They do not always drop the Decayed 

armor.
</P>
<B>Manr, level 29 Dark Elf Shadow Knight on Povar</B>

			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
			</tr>
